result.execSummary:
The defendant Brittany N. Fellenz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: All fines and costs are to be paid directly to the Taylor County Clerk of Courts Office in the amount of $50 a month beginning November 1, 2022. Failure to pay may result in a civil judgment being entered against you, tax intercept, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant shall submit to a DNA sample at the Taylor County Sheriff's Department.

3:05 PM Defendant Brittany N. Fellenz in court.  Attorney Nicholas Grant Smith in court for Brittany N. Fellenz.  Attorney Kristi S. Tlusty in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Tlusty recites agreement for the record. Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 2 resisting and obstructing an officer. Plea colloquy. Plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently; factual basis exists for the plea.  Court makes a finding of guilt on Count 2. Court dismisses but read in count 1 as well as dismisses but reads in the tracking citations of 22TR415, 22TR416, 22TR417, 22TR418. Statement made by Attorney Tlusty. Statement made by Attorney Smith. Court orders a $200.00 fine plus court costs along with the DNA sample and surcharge. Defendant is to make payments to the Taylor County Clerk of Courts Office in the amount of $50.00 a month beginning November 1, 2022.-JN
